rComments: Favourite professor from my undergrad. Great guy and cares about students' success.
omg, this prof is a solid instructor. Don't take this class if you don't like to think critically. So different that all the others. He opens your eyes - and he cares.
Horrible professor. Extremely inconsistent with his materials, very poor teaching quality. Takes things to a personal level. Avoid at all costs, take Inez Blackburn's section instead.

AMAZING lectures (unique lecture format)! You get graded on participation (must participate every class) will get ample opportunity to talk so don't worry about that. He includes real life example and gives his students a lot of good career and life advice. Not many assessments but they are graded fairly (2 case studies, exam, and a presentation)
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters']
